                            <comment id="17251714" author="davsclaus" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2020 11:32:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you only want to include .txt files, then use include option. &lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://camel.apache.org/components/2.x/file-component.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://camel.apache.org/components/2.x/file-component.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Mind include is a regexp pattern, so use include=.*txt&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17251739" author="kstam" created="Fri, 18 Dec 2020 12:30:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t support that feature in Syndesis (yet). I can&apos;t do it this way?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
